Grand Union Hotel, located at Fourth Avenue and 42nd Street, just across the street from the Grand Central Station. It was Closed May 2nd, 1934.

About 1914

722197f-a.text:
Park avenue, south and including 43rd street, seen from the roof of 230 Park Avenue, the New York Central building. The Lincoln Building 60 East 42nd Street, opposite the foot of Vanderbilt Avenue, is shown nearly completed.

1929
N. Lazarnick
